rikes, and varied organizing strategies to find common ground among California’s diverse communities and achieve a measure of economic fairness and social justice. This is an indispensible book for students and scholars of labor history and history of the West, as well as labor activists and organizers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aLabor movementzCaliforniaxHistory. 0aLabor unionszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aLaborzCaliforniaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  acalifornia history.  acalifornia labor history.  acalifornia labor politics.  acalifornia labor strikes.  acalifornia unions.  acalifornia workers collective bargaining.  acalifornia workers rights.  agold rush.  ahistory of workers rights since the gold rush.  alabor history.  alabor movement.  alabor politics.  alabor strikes.  alabor studies.  aorganizing strategies.  arace and labor in california.  aunion history.  aworkers rights.  aworking class.  aworking immigrants.  aworking people.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028840940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096334440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963344423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963344/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY